article.description: Luka Brajkovic scored 14 points to lead six Davidson players in double figures and the Wildcats defeated Central Pennsylvania 88-54 on Saturday.
article.headline: Davidson beats Central Penn with 6 players in double-figures
article.linkText: Davidson beats Central Penn with 6 players in double-figures
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Luka Brajkovic scored 14 points to lead six Davidson players in double figures and the Wildcats defeated Central Pennsylvania 88-54 on Saturday. Brajkovic grabbed 11 rebounds in posting his third career double-double. Luke Frampton, who had four 3-pointers, Carter Collins, David Czerapowicz and Bates Jones scored 12 points apiece with Jon Axel Gudmundsson adding 10. The Wildcats (9-3) snapped a two-game skid and improved to 6-0 at home. They shot 50 percent, outscored the Knights 48-21 in the paint, made 11 of 37 3-point shots and had a 51-27 rebounding advantage. Joel Zola had 12 points and 10 rebounds and Deon Tabb 12 points for the Knights, who play in the United State Collegiate Athletic Association. Davidson took a 47-21 lead at halftime behind 10 points each from Brajkovic and Gudmundsson and led by as many as 41 in the second half.
